<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - INJECTION PUMP, NOZZLES, FUEL FILTER, SUPPLY PUMP AND GLOW PLUGS -
        Removing Injection Pump (all applications) - REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Injection Pump Gear Installation (With Front Cover Installed)</title>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>PRIOR TO REASSEMBLY BE SURE ALL MATING SURFACES ARE CLEAN AND FREE OF EITHER GASKET MATERIAL
                        OR R.T.V. SEALANT.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install injection pump drive gear as follows:</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If a new gear is being installed, mark the new gear in reference to the "Y" mark stamped
                            on the front of the gear. (Refer to Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350939">9.39</hotlnk>.)
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the injection pump drive gear to the camshaft gear with the reference line
                        at six o'clock.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Be sure the "Y" mark reference line on the injection pump drive gear mates in
                        between the two dyed gear teeth of the camshaft gear. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e435_192.xml" xrefid="ef4350938">9.38</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <important>
                            <para>VERIFY THAT NO.1 PISTON IS AT TDC PRIOR TO INSTALLING THE INJECTION PUMP DRIVE GEAR.
                            </para>
                        </important>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a 1/8 in. dia. bead of R.T.V. sealant into the narrow groove at the bottom and
                    sides of the gear tower; and a 3/16 in. diameter bead across the front of the gear tower. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350940">9.40</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>ASSEMBLE COMPONENTS WITHIN 15 MINUTES OF R.T.V. APPLICATION. IF SEALANT "SETS UP" IT LOSES
                            ITS SEALING EFFECTIVENESS.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the adapter housing over the injection pump drive gear and tighten the four
                    mounting bolts. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350941">9.41</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>With the injection pump adapter housing mounted to the engine, the injection drive gear
                            drive cannot "jump" timing.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4350939" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12412" filename="../figcg1/cg12412.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.39</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350940" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11188" filename="../figcg1/cg11188.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.40</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350941" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12400" filename="../figcg1/cg12400.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.41</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
